                <h1>I survived<br>Clippy.</h1>

                <div class="about-content" style="margin-top: 6rem;">
                    <div class="about-text">
                        <p>It started with WordArt tutorials from my dad and Lemmings sessions after school, back when 56k was broadband, MSN was the chat, and Netflix was eMule.</p>
                        <p>From album covers for Turin's emerging hip hop and electronic scene, to photo retouching for diving and swimming competitions across northern Italy, to agency life, where I learned how digital communication actually works at scale. Small shops finding their voice, global corporates reaching thousands of employees across five continents. Both ends of the spectrum, same attention.</p>
                        <p>I've always run experiments and personal projects on the side, and I'll keep doing so. My place is in a tech/creative team that values curiosity over job titles.</p>
                        <p style="font-size:1rem; color: var(--accent);">Off the clock: video games (you don't say?), bagna cauda, a local artisan market, and fishing. My family calls me "the brand manager". I take every product launch very seriously, including dinner.</p>

